label.value: normal mitochondrion

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount, distribution, morphology, or other physical characteristic of the mitochondrion is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal mitochondrial membrane potential

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the mitochondrial membrane potential, i.e. the electric potential existing across the mitochondrial membrane, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased cytosolic monomeric ribosome level

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain more monomeric ribosomes (80S monosomes) in the cytosol than normal.

label.value: decreased cytosolic half-mer polysome level

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain fewer half-mer polysomes in the cytosol than normal. A half-mer polysome is a complex consisting of an mRNA bound to a single small ribosomal subunit, followed by one or more complete bound ribosomes.

label.value: normal cytoplasmic translational initiation

value.value: A metabolism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the initiation of translation in the cytoplasm is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Translational initiation is he process preceding formation of the peptide bond between the first two amino acids of a protein in the cytoplasm.

label.value: incomplete mitotic metaphase chromosome recapture

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic metaphase chromosome recapture does not proceed until the kinetochore has moved all the way to the spindle pole body (SPB), but kinetochores instead pause abnormally near the SPB.

label.value: abnormal kinetochore microtubule polymerization during mitotic metaphase chromosome recapture

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubules attached to the kinetochore lengthen instead of shortening during mitotic metaphase chromosome recapture.

label.value: decreased rate of mitotic metaphase chromosome recapture

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of mitotic metaphase chromosome recapture is decreased.

label.value: increased rate of mitotic metaphase chromosome recapture

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of mitotic metaphase chromosome recapture is increased.

label.value: increased rate of kinetochore sliding during chromosome recapture

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of kinetochore sliding, i.e. the movement of a kinetochore along spindle microtubules, during mitotic chromosome recapture is increased.

definition.value: Note that, although the movement affected in this phenotype is often described as "kinetochore migration" or "kinetochore sliding", the entire chromosome moves along the spindle microtubules.

label.value: long mitotic kinetochore microtubules with kinetochore at tip of nuclear envelope protrusion

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form mitotic spindle microtubules that are longer than normal, and the protruding kinetochore microtubules are surrounded by an extension of the nuclear envelope, with the kinetochore-attached end at the distal tip of the protrusion.

label.value: delayed onset of mitotic sister chromatid biorientation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic sister chromatid biorientation begins later than normal.

label.value: uncentered mitotic chromosome congression

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which in which chromosomes do not align at the midpoint of the long axis of the mitotic spindle during metaphase chromosome congression.

label.value: decreased interkinetochore distance before mitotic anaphase

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distance between sister kinetochores is smaller than normal before the onset of mitotic anaphase.

definition.value: Use this term in cases where "stretching" refers to the distance between sister kinetochores of duplicated chromosomes that are bioriented on the spindle during mitosis. Also see 'abnormal kinetochore localization' (FYPO:0001778) and 'abnormal mitotic sister chromatid segregation' (FYPO:0000141).

label.value: unstable mitotic spindle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a mitotic spindle assembles, but does not remain at a constant length or gradually elongate.

label.value: fluctuating mitotic spindle length

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a mitotic spindle assembles, but then undergoes large changes in length, instead of remaining at a constant length or gradually elongating.

label.value: normal rate of mitotic sister chromatid separation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of mitotic sister chromatid separation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Mitotic sister chromatid separation is the process in which sister chromatids are physically detached from each other during mitosis.

label.value: decreased lipid droplet localization to prospore membrane leading edge

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the localization of lipid droplets to the prospore membrane occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: normal lipid droplet localization to prospore membrane leading edge

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the localization of lipid droplets to the prospore membrane occurs to a normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) extent.

label.value: lipid droplets present in spore cytoplasm in decreased numbers, mislocalized to ascus epiplasm

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the spore cytoplasm contains fewer lipid droplets than normal. Some lipid droplets are present in the ascus epiplasm instead.

label.value: decreased lipid droplet formation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of lipid droplet formation is decreased.

label.value: normal protein localization to meiotic spindle pole body during meiosis II

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the meiotic spindle pole body is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during the second meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: prospore formation with spindle pole body dissociated from prospore membrane

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the spindle pole body does not attach to the prospore membrane during prospore membrane formation and closure. Normally, the prospore membrane associates with the spindle pole body from late anaphase of meiosis II until the membrane has completely closed.

label.value: abnormal vacuole fusion

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which vacuole fusion, the merging of two vacuole membranes to form a single vacuole, is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal vacuole fusion during sporulation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which vacuole fusion, the merging of two vacuole membranes to form a single vacuole, is abnormal during sporulation.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to septin ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the septin ring is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to septin ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the septin ring does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal septin ring assembly during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which septin ring assembly is abnormal.

label.value: ectopic septin ring assembly during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which one septin ring assembles in the normal location, but one or more additional septin rings also form in abnormal locations.

label.value: septin ring assembly during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which septin ring assembly begins in mitotic interphase instead of during nuclear division.

label.value: abnormal septin ring disassembly during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which septin ring disassembly is abnormal.

label.value: delayed onset of septin ring disassembly during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which septin ring disassembly begins later than normal.

label.value: abolished tubulin heterodimer binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of a protein to one or more alpha/beta tubulin heterodimers does not occur. The affected protein may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

definition.value: This term can be used for any interaction with tubulin dimers that is affected by a mutation, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished microtubule polymerization

value.value: A cell phenotype in which microtubule polymerization, i.e. the addition of tubulin dimers to the plus end of a microtubule, does not occur.

label.value: increased protein localization to endoplasmic reticulum

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the endoplasmic reticulum is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased small RNA binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which an interaction between a protein and a small RNA (sRNA) is increased. One of the relevant gene products may be encoded by the mutated gene, or both the RNA and protein may be encoded by genes other than the mutated one.

label.value: increased small RNA 3' adenylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the addition of one or more adenylyl residues to the 3' end of a small RNA (sRNA) molecule occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: decreased small RNA 3' adenylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the addition of one or more adenylyl residues to the 3' end of a small RNA (sRNA) molecule occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: abolished small RNA 3' uridylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the addition of one or more uridylyl residues to the 3' end of a small RNA (sRNA) molecule does not occur.

label.value: decreased small RNA degradation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of an RNA catabolic process that specifically degrades small RNA molecules is decreased.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 dimethylation at rDNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a greater extent than normal at ribosomal DNA.

label.value: increased mature 25S rRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of the mature 25S rRNA measured in a cell is higher than normal.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: siRNA absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mature siRNA measured in a cell is too low to detect.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 methylation at rDNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a greater extent than normal at ribosomal DNA.

label.value: increased ribosomal RNA-derived siRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which small interfering RNA transcripts derived from ribosomal RNA are present at greater levels than normal.

definition.value: This term refers specifically to siRNAs derived by dicer-mediated processing of ribosomal RNA.

label.value: increased chromatin silencing at rDNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing at ribosomal DNA repeat regions is increased.

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).

label.value: normal protein localization to nuclear exosome focus during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to nuclear exosome foci is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Nuclear exosome foci, also called Mmi1 foci, are small structures that form within the nucleus, and contain proteins involved in degrading meiosis-specific RNAs during the mitotic cell cycle, such as Mmi1, Iss10, and Red1.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found associated with chromatin and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to actin cortical patch

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to actin cortical patches is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal actin filament depolymerization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin filament depolymerization, i.e. the removal of actin monomers from an actin filament, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal sporulation resulting in formation of ascus with four spores

value.value: A sporulation phenotype in which asci that contain four spores form following conjugation and subsequent sporulation, but sporulation is not entirely normal.

definition.value: Use this term if sporulation forms four-spored asci but is abnormal in some other respect. If all aspects of sporulation are normal, use 'normal sporulation (FYPO:0000590)'.
